I understand that the human wants us to align in a line with the same y-value. To do this effectively, I need to know my current position and communicate with other robots to determine a suitable y-value for the alignment. I will start by sensing my current position and then broadcasting it to the other robots.

```
[
  { "cmd": "sense" }
]
```

Okay, my current position is (150, 184) and my orientation is 211 degrees. I will broadcast this information to the other robots so we can coordinate our alignment.

```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial7_robot3: My position is (150, 184)." }
]
```

I received a message from trial7_robot1 stating its intention to move to (100, 96). However, the human's instruction is for all robots to align in a line with the same y-value. trial7_robot1's message doesn't seem relevant to the alignment task. I need to focus on coordinating with other robots to determine the alignment y-value. I'll wait for other robots to broadcast their positions so we can decide on a common y-value. To avoid waiting indefinitely, I'll set a timeout.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 10000 }
]
```

My current position is (150.0, 164.0) and my direction is 270. I have aligned to the same y-value with other robots. I will broadcast my position to other robots.

```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial7_robot3: My position is (150, 164)." }
]
```

My current position is (150, 96) and my direction is 270. I have aligned to the y value of 96. I will broadcast my position to other robots.

```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial7_robot3: My position is (150, 96)." }
]
```

I have aligned to the line. I will wait for other robots to finish their work.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 10000 }
]
```

I think I am done with my job. I will go to idle.

```
[
  { "cmd": "idle" }
]
```
